-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dpo1665702828359.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dpo1665702828359.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dpo1665702828359.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dpo1665702828359\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                          \n Define HTML Widget Properties\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define the properties for this HTML Widget.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpo1665702828359__p_d9032e1_d9033e1_d9034e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ied1665702642247.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ied1665702642247.html\" title=\"The uhtml widget is a field-level widget in a form component that renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page (when the field value is a URL prefixed by an ampersand (&amp;www.mysite.com/doc/index.html). Uniface provides a logical widget called HTML, which is mapped to uhtml.\">uhtml (HTML Widget)</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dpo1665702828359__section_qq4_j2k_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d122068e70\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dpo1665702828359__ul_nqs_j2k_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpo1665702828359__li_d4103e1_d4104e1_d4105e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpo1665702828359__p_d9038e1_d9039e1_d9040e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mae1704708062818.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mae1704708062818.html\" title=\"You can set widget properties in several ways—in the initialization file used by the application, in the IDE using the Properties Inspector, or in script. And you can set them in modeled entities, in component templates, in components, and in script.\">Setting Widget Properties</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjk1665702557273.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widgets</a><p>In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526921\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526921\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" cl